cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CY 

This paper discusses the problem of extracting keywords from parked domains to display relevant advertisements. This involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques, which are commonly studied in the sub-categories of Information Retrieval (cs.IR), Computational Linguistics (cs.CL), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Machine Learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the use of multi-armed bandits for contextual advertising is a topic that falls under the sub-category of Cybernetics (cs.CY).
